## Overview

The AK-series robotic actuator from CubeMars uses two primary communication interfaces:
- **CAN Bus**: Primary interface for real-time control and feedback
- **Serial Port (UART)**: Secondary interface for configuration and debugging

The driver board adopts Field Oriented Control (FOC) algorithm with advanced self-disturbance control technology for speed and angle control.

### Supported Driver Models
| Model | Rated Current (RMS) | Max Current (Ap) | Size |
|-------|-------------------|-----------------|------|
| AK54-4810-1C-A2 | 10A | 30A | 54mm × 54mm |
| AK60-4820-1C-A2 | 20A | 60A | 63mm × 57mm |
| AK80-4830-1C-A4 | 30A | 90A | 76.33mm × 85mm |

### General Specifications
- **Allowable input voltage**: 48V
- **Working voltage range**: 18-52V
- **CAN bus bitrate**: Up to 1Mbps
- **Inner-loop encoder resolution**: 21-bit (single-loop absolute)
- **Operating temperature**: -20°C to 65°C
- **Max driver board temperature**: 100°C

