## CAN Bus Protocol

### Frame Structure

The CAN protocol uses **Extended Frame** format with 8 bytes of data.

#### CAN ID Structure
```
|<-- bits [28]-[8] -->|<-- bits [7]-[0] -->|
|   Control Mode ID    |       Drive ID     |
```

**CAN ID = (Control_Mode_ID << 8) | Drive_ID**

### Control Mode IDs

| Mode ID | Control Mode | Description |
|---------|-------------|-------------|
| 0 | Duty Cycle Mode | Set duty cycle voltage |
| 1 | Current Loop Mode | Set Iq current (torque) |
| 2 | Current Brake Mode | Set braking current |
| 3 | Velocity Loop Mode | Set operating speed |
| 4 | Position Loop Mode | Set target position |
| 5 | Setting Origin Mode | Set zero position |
| 6 | Position-Velocity Loop Mode | Set position, speed, and acceleration |
| 8 | Force Control (MIT) Mode | Force control mode |
| 15 | Motor Disable Mode | Disable motor output |
| 16 | Feedback Message Configuration | Configure feedback frames |

### Function IDs (Feedback Messages)

| Function ID | Description |
|-------------|-------------|
| 0x2C | Start frame (sent when motor enters servo mode) |
| 0x29 | Real-time status feedback frame |
| 0x2A | Optional 4-byte position feedback frame |

