## Serial Port Protocol

### Frame Format

```
| Header | Data Length | Data Frame | Checksum (High) | Checksum (Low) | Tail |
| 0xAA   | 1-2 bytes   | Variable   | 1 byte          | 1 byte         | 0xBB |
```

**Header**: `0xAA` (for ≤256 bytes) or `0xAB` (for >256 bytes)
**Data Length**: Excludes header, checksum, and tail
**Checksum**: CRC-16 (see CRC calculation below)
**Tail**: `0xBB`

### Serial Command IDs

| ID | Command | Description |
|----|---------|-------------|
| 60 | COMM_SET_POS_SPD | Position-Velocity Loop Mode |
| 61 | COMM_SET_POS_MULTI | Multi-circle motion mode |
| 62 | COMM_SET_POS_SINGLE | Single-circle motion mode |
| 63 | COMM_SET_POS_UNLIMITED | Unlimited position mode |
| 64 | COMM_SET_POS_ORIGIN | Set motor origin |
| 65 | COMM_FW_VERSION | Firmware version |
| 66 | COMM_JUMP_TO_BOOTLOADER | Jump to bootloader |
| 67 | COMM_ERASE_NEW_APP | Erase new app |
| 68 | COMM_WRITE_NEW_APP_DATA | Write new app data |
| 69 | COMM_GET_VALUES | Get motor operating parameters |
| 70 | COMM_SET_DUTY | Duty cycle mode |
| 71 | COMM_SET_CURRENT | Current loop mode |
| 72 | COMM_SET_CURRENT_BRAKE | Current brake mode |
| 73 | COMM_SET_RPM | Velocity loop mode |
| 74 | COMM_SET_POS | Position loop mode |
| 75 | COMM_SET_HANDBRAKE | Handbrake current loop mode |
| 76 | COMM_SET_DETECT | Real-time position feedback |
| 87 | COMM_ROTOR_POSITION | Feedback current position |
| 16 | COMM_GET_VALUES_SETUP | Setup for getting values |

### CRC-16 Calculation

```c
const unsigned short crc16_tab[] = {
    0x0000, 0x1021, 0x2042, 0x3063, 0x4084, 0x50a5, 0x60c6, 0x70e7,
    0x8108, 0x9129, 0xa14a, 0xb16b, 0xc18c, 0xd1ad, 0xe1ce, 0xf1ef,
    // ... (full 256-entry table in manual)
};

unsigned short crc16(unsigned char *buf, unsigned int len) {
    unsigned short cksum = 0;
    for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {
        cksum = crc16_tab[(((cksum >> 8) ^ buf[i]) & 0xFF)] ^ (cksum << 8);
    }
    return cksum;
}
```

