## Feedback Messages

### CAN Feedback Frame (ID 0x29)

The motor sends real-time status via timed upload mode. Upload frequency is configurable (1-2000 Hz).

**CAN ID**: `(0x29 << 8) | Drive_ID`

**8-Byte Data Format**:
```
| Byte | Content |
|------|---------|
| Data[0] | Position high byte |
| Data[1] | Position low byte |
| Data[2] | Speed high byte |
| Data[3] | Speed low byte |
| Data[4] | Current high byte |
| Data[5] | Current low byte |
| Data[6] | Motor temperature |
| Data[7] | Error code |
```

**Decoding Formulas**:
```c
// Position (int16, range -32000 to 32000)
Position = (int16) / 10.0  // Result in degrees (-3200° to 3200°)

// Speed (int16, range -32000 to 32000)
Speed = (int16) * 10.0  // Result in ERPM (-320000 to 320000)

// Current (int16, range -6000 to 6000)
Current = (int16) * 0.01  // Result in Amperes (-60A to 60A)

// Temperature (int8, range -20 to 127)
Temperature = (int8)  // Result in °C

// Error Code (uint8)
Error = Data[7]
```

**Example Receiver Function**:
```c
void motor_receive(float *pos, float *spd, float *cur, int8_t *temp, uint8_t *error, rx_msg) {
    int16_t pos_int = (rx_msg->Data[0] << 8) | rx_msg->Data[1];
    int16_t spd_int = (rx_msg->Data[2] << 8) | rx_msg->Data[3];
    int16_t cur_int = (rx_msg->Data[4] << 8) | rx_msg->Data[5];
    
    *pos = pos_int * 0.1f;
    *spd = spd_int * 10.0f;
    *cur = cur_int * 0.01f;
    *temp = rx_msg->Data[6];
    *error = rx_msg->Data[7];
}
```

### Optional Extended Position Frame (ID 0x2A)

When configured via Feedback Message Configuration command, an additional 4-byte position frame is sent.

**CAN ID**: `(0x2A << 8) | Drive_ID`

**Data Format** (4 bytes, int32):
```
| Data[0] | Data[1] | Data[2] | Data[3] |
| Bit 25-32 | Bit 17-24 | Bit 9-16 | Bit 1-8 |
```

**Formula**: `Position = (int32) / 100.0`
**Range**: -21,474,836.48° to 21,474,836.47°

